cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper is primarily focused on image processing algorithms, specifically pooling mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object recognition and image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a biologically inspired mechanism for contrast-variant pooling, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NI (Neuroscience and Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on colour constancy, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
